<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="520" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,500]" pageId="9" pageNumber="520">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,260,285]" pageId="9" pageNumber="520">Etymology</emphasis>
. The name 
<taxonomicName box="[460,538,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Anapeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tumida">
<emphasis box="[460,538,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="520">tumida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a Latin adjective meaning swollen, in reference to the enlarged fused female cerci that cover the entire posterior end of the abdomen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,500]" pageId="9" pageNumber="520">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,346,332,357]" pageId="9" pageNumber="520">Life history.</emphasis>
This species forms circular, flat, blisterlike epidermal galls, about 
<quantity box="[1133,1202,332,356]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="520" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
in diameter, on the underside of leaves of 
<taxonomicName box="[401,679,368,392]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Psychotria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="9" pageNumber="520" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mapourioides">
<emphasis box="[401,679,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="520">Psychotria mapourioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Each gall is inhabited by a single larva that pupates in the gall. The pupa pushes its way out of the thin-walled gall and the adult breaks out of the pupa. Adult emergence takes place from 
<number box="[212,278,440,464]" pageId="9" pageNumber="520" value="8.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="8.0">8 to 9</number>
a.m. Several generations occur per year. Galls may be found on the same leaves as those of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Pellacara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="postica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="520">Pellacara postica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
